---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../site.config';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={`About ${siteConfig.title}`}>
	<section class="page-intro">
		<span class="eyebrow">About</span>
		<h1>A cleaner Project Euler archive.</h1>
		<p>
			This version of the site is built around Project Euler first: the goal is to make long
			mathematical solutions and the matching C++ and Python code easy to browse years later.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section-panel">
		<div class="track-grid">
			<div class="card" data-tone="warm">
				<h3>Why the archive is problem-first</h3>
				<p>
					Project Euler pages are the core unit now, not a side category. Each problem gets a
					full explanation and its source files on a dedicated page.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card" data-tone="cool">
				<h3>Why both languages are visible</h3>
				<p>
					The C++ and Python versions solve different needs. Seeing them together makes it much
					easier to compare performance-oriented and clarity-oriented implementations.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card" data-tone="olive">
				<h3>Why the layout changed</h3>
				<p>
					The site was reshaped to feel more intentional: stronger hierarchy, better cards,
					searchable archive controls, and source code that stays on the same page as the proof.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
